<item>
            <title>[LU-8278] sanity-scrub test_4b: Error in dmesg detected</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-8278</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This issue was created by maloo for Doug Oucharek &amp;lt;doug.s.oucharek@intel.com&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue relates to the following test suite run: &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/90878f52-3273-11e6-bbf5-5254006e85c2&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/90878f52-3273-11e6-bbf5-5254006e85c2&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The sub-test test_4b failed with the following error:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;Error in dmesg detected
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Seems the test is getting this dmesg: &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;11801.222399&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; VFS: Busy inodes after unmount of dm-3. Self-destruct in 5 seconds.  Have a nice day...&lt;/p&gt;</description>
